{"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"kind":"symbol","sections":[],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/SignalGroupSignalName\/notify","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glibobject\/signalgroupsignalname\/notify"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The notify signal is emitted on an object when one of its properties has"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"its value set through "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_object_set_property()"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"code":"g_object_set()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", et al.","type":"text"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"case"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"notify"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"discussion","type":"heading","text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Note that getting this signal doesn’t itself guarantee that the value of","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the property has actually changed. When it is emitted is determined by the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"derived GObject class. If the implementor did not create the property with","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"explicitNotify"},{"type":"text","text":", then any call to "},{"code":"g_object_set_property()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" results","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"in "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"notify"},{"type":"text","text":" being emitted, even if the new value is the same as the old."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"If they did pass "},{"code":"explicitNotify","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", then this signal is emitted only","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"when they explicitly call "},{"code":"g_object_notify()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_object_notify_by_pspec()"},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"and common practice is to do that only when the value has actually changed."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This signal is typically used to obtain change notification for a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"single property, by specifying the property name as a detail in the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_signal_connect()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" call, like this:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"(C Language Example):","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["g_signal_connect (text_view->buffer, \"notify::paste-target-list\",","                  G_CALLBACK (gtk_text_view_target_list_notify),","                  text_view)"],"syntax":"C"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It is important to note that you must use"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"#class@GObject.ParamSpec#parameter-names","type":"reference"},{"text":" as","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"detail strings for the notify signal."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"metadata":{"role":"symbol","symbolKind":"case","fragments":[{"text":"case","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"notify","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"SignalGroupSignalName.notify","modules":[{"name":"GLibObject"}],"externalID":"s:10GLibObject011SignalGroupC4NameO6notifyyA2CmF","roleHeading":"Case"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/SignalGroupSignalName"]]},"references":{"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject/SignalGroupSignalName/notify":{"type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"The notify signal is emitted on an object when one of its properties has"